                    "<b>The sons of Aharon.</b> And not the daughters of Aharon. Rambam wrote in Hilchos Aveil that this is the reason why women are not obligated to become impure for the dead. [Only] the males are commanded to become impure for them. Since they are not included in the prohibition of “let him not defile himself with the dead,” therefore they are not subject to the commandment of becoming impure …"
